      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PASTOR DUNBAR (5) came from wider for a win at this circuit when resuming two back then copped a check and broke last start so did well to recover for a 2m second. A good draw should see him hard to stop. TIMMY WHIZ (1) chased along the sprint lane and finished third when resuming at Maryborough last week. Will be fitter and gets the ace draw so must be considered. STEPBYSTEP (9) hasn't been far from the placings in two starts since a spell. His lone career win came when third up over this distance so could do it again. LEO GALLEON (11) made an encouraging return when runner-up and could progress.",
